filters
Class NCBIBlastFactory

java.lang.Object
  filters.NCBIBlastFactory

public class NCBIBlastFactory
extends java.lang.Object

This is the factory class for using the NCBI Blast algorithm. To perform a remote Blast the class uses filters.NCBIBlastGetCommand to retrieve an Rid identifier and then calls filters.NCBIBlastPutCommand to retrieve results using the Rid. The results are processed by searching for alignment lengths between target & query(Oligo) sequences, and by retrieving a uniqueness value for each query sequence. Based off these values an Oligo sequence either passes or fails. The alignment length required is 20, w/ no gaps. An Oligo must be unique (i.e. have no more than 1 hit).

parseBlast

private void parseBlast(java.lang.String result)
Parses a String representing the NCBI blast output. Splits the String into separate strings by locating each query, and then cycles through each query looking for the number of hits present and the alignment length. This algorithm uses pattern matching to determine the align length for an oligo query with a target query by counting the number of pipe symbols ("|") in a row, each of which represent a single alignment between nucleotides. Each oligo that does not meet the filter requirements is "rejected" and the entire list of oligos is returned from the blast method.

Parameters:
result - - output from the NCBI Blast server.

batchQueries

protected java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> batchQueries()
Combines query strings into batches to minimize the number of blast requests to the server. Every batch is equals in size and is determined by the limits of the blast server.

Returns:
- a list containing "batches" of query sequences.

addBatch

protected java.lang.String addBatch(int start,
                                    int end)
Creates a batch of oligos from a start and end index. Each Oligo object is identified by its location in validOligos; this location is stored in the Fasta header for the sequence. The ordering that each sequence is added is extremely important because it determines later which Oligos are filtered out by the BlastFilter.

Parameters:
start - - index that represents the location to start this batch of oligos of the oligo list.
end -
Returns:
batch - a batch of multifasta sequences.
